	<h2>Submitting Player Characters</h2>
	<p class="left_align">At this time, neither SmashGG or Challonge has the information within a tournament bracket to allow us to know which character you play. Adding the stock head icon next to a tag on either the index and player page requires manual input from us. If you would like your character to be represented next to your name, fill out our <a href="{{url_for('submit_form_unsubmitted')}}">form</a> and select "Add my character/color".</p>

	<h2>Managing Alternate Tags</h2>
	<p class="left_align">Players entering tournaments with different tags can be merged in our system. However, we will not actively hunt down players who choose to enter under fake tags. If you want your ranking to represented in an accurate and timely fashion, please enter as your normal tag. If you have any player merge requests, please fill out our <a href="{{url_for('submit_form_unsubmitted')}}">contact form.</a></p>

	<h2>Handling Inactive Players</h2>
	<p class="left_align">The Washington Power Ranking Panel has designated an activity requirement of 4 tournaments within the ranking period (3-4 months)to be eligible for PR. We use a similar but more variable requirement based on the frequency of tournaments occuring within our region. Generally, we require one tournament within the past month to be considered active. If you do not meet this requirement, you will be hidden from the global ranking page but still searchable on our site.</p> 





